- FEATURE: Add multi-threading support for heavy background work (for example directory scanning/search indexing), with thread-safe state handling and unchanged editor behavior.
- FEATURE: Add "Go to definition" for functions (jump from call site to declaration/definition), including keyboard action and a fallback picker when multiple matches exist.
- FEATURE: Add Language Server Protocol (LSP) client support (server lifecycle, document sync, and `textDocument/definition`) to enable accurate cross-file "Go to definition" and future language features.
- FEATURE: Add drawer-local file search by filename/path (via `find`/`fzf`) with live filtering, keyboard navigation, and open-on-select behavior.
- FEATURE: Add project-wide text search (via `grep`/`rg`) with a results list that supports jump-to-match and next/previous result navigation.
- FEATURE: Add find-and-replace workflows (current file and project scope) with preview, replace-one, replace-all, and undo-safe behavior.
- FEATURE: Add configurable auto-indentation (tabs/spaces + indent width) for newline insertion and pasted blocks.
- FEATURE: Add bracket/quote pair assistance: auto-close pairs, skip-over closing pairs, and jump to matching bracket.
- FEATURE: Add line numbers and current-line highlight (toggleable) to improve code navigation and context.
- FEATURE: implement support for vim-mode. The commands should be configurable in .rotide.toml in local and global files.
